'''1st [[Marine Expeditionary Brigade]]''' (MEB) is a unit in the [[I Marine Expeditionary Force]] (I MEF) and is the "middleweight" global crisis response force. It is able to "operate independently, as a service component, or to lead a Joint Task Force"{{Citation needed|date=July 2009}}.
==History== The brigade was stationed at [[Marine Corps Base Hawaii|Kaneohe Bay Marine Corps Air Station]] until 1992. From 1976 to 1981 while at Kaneohe (now known as Marine Corps Base Hawaii), the unit was designated as the 1st Marine Brigade. In addition to the Brigade Headquarters Group as its [[Command Element]] (CE), the 1st Marine Brigade consisted of the [[3rd Marine Regiment]] as its [[Ground Combat Element]] (GCE), [[Marine Aircraft Group 24]] (MAG-24) as its [[Aviation Combat Element]] (ACE), and a Brigade Service Support Group (BSSG) as it [[Logistics Combat Element]] (CLE).
==Organization== * [[Command Element]] - [[Battalion]] equivalent [[Headquarters#Military|headquarters]] organization, formed of [[Company (military unit)|companies]]/[[Detachment (military)|detachments]] sourced from the parent MEF HQ Group and [[Staff (military)|staff]], and with the Deputy MEF Commander as the MEB Commander. * [[Ground Combat Element]] - [[Regimental Combat Team#U.S. Marine Corps|Regimental Combat Team]] (RCT) consisting of a reinforced Marine Infantry Regiment. * [[Aviation Combat Element]] - [[United States Marine Corps Aviation#Groups|Marine Aircraft Group]] (MAG), consisting of a combination of rotary-wing, tiltrotor, and/or fixed wing [[List of United States Marine Corps aircraft squadrons|aircraft squadrons/detachments]] and [[List of United States Marine Corps aviation support units|aviation support squadrons/detachments]], capable of conducting all six functions of [[United States Marine Corps Aviation|Marine aviation]] including [[close air support|offensive air support]], [[assault support]], [[electronic warfare]], [[command and control|control of aircraft and missiles]], [[anti-air warfare]] and [[aerial reconnaissance]]. * [[Logistics Combat Element]] - Combat Logistics Regiment (CLR), consisting of from 1 to 3 Combat Logistics Battalions (CLB) and capable of providing full-spectrum [[Combat Service Support#United States Marine Corps|Combat Service Support]] to all elements of the MEB.
